					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Gila monsters can spend more than 95 percent of their lives underground. They emerge to feed only a few times a year and to bask in the desert sun. They can store fat in their oversized tails and go months between meals!
						</text>
