				<title>
					Home Base
				</title>
				<navigationLabel>
					Home Base
				</navigationLabel>
				<contentItems>
					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Gila monsters are found in the southwestern United States, all the way down to Mexico. Their range includes parts of Arizona, California, Nevada, Utah and New Mexico. Gila monsters prefer scrubland, succulent desert, and woodlands where they can shelter in burrows, thickets and under rocks. They do need access to moisture in order to survive.
						</text>
